narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: Learnt a lot about key debates in the philosophy of science

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: Strengths - great readings, great professor, generally good seminar participants Weaknesses - the course does get confusing especially when one isn't familiar with the writings/key debates at the onset. So sometimes it's clear during the seminar that people aren't engaging as much because they're probably confused...

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Yes - rather insightful seminar, although you may get lost in all the readings/discussions if you aren't sufficiently clear about what's going on. Anyway, light workload, useful readings, and good prof!
